ch Protestantism was born and where it can reach, and expresses great admiration for its most prominent thinkers and spiritual leaders, including Jonathan Edwards, Horace Bushnell, Walter Rauschenbusch, Reinhold Niebuhr, and Paul Tillich. Further testament to Giussani's clear-minded and comprehensive knowledge of Christianity, American Protestant Theology makes the work of a master theologian available in English for the first time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aProtestant churcheszUnited StatesxDoctrinesxHistory. 0aTheology, DoctrinalzUnited StatesxHistory. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh1 aBacich, Damian, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aGiussani, Luigi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpencer, Archibald J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358951340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773589513423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773589513/original  a978-3-11-127412-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013b2013  a978-3-11-127715-8  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles